title: Samplestate.Love.Not.Money.Presents.Deep.House.Garage.and.Nu.Dis
description:
Love Not Money Presents - Deep House Garage & Nu Disco
Genres: Bass House, Deep House and Garage
Formats: Apple Loops, Rex2 and Wav



In a time where many new, young labels are vying for the attention of the music-buying public, and of course, trying to work their way into every DJ's record box Ã¢â‚¬â€œ Love Not Money has made quite an impression.

The Leeds-based label, helmed by Luke Pompey, has released a steady catalogue of quality music from a range of talented, and mostly new artists. The label has become a reputable source of good music in a short space of time while maintaining a high quality and a slick approach to everything they do.

Since launching in late 2011 Love Not Money have already found their feet among the dance elite. They've signed over 100 artists, are close to their 40th release and have gained support from DJ's the world over. They've had plays worldwide on BBC Radio 1, Capital FM and Ibiza Global Radio and have racked up 15 Beatport top 100's, 1 Nu-Disco No.2.

Here they present to you a crossed-genre sample pack containing an array of rich musical elements and sounds from Deep House, Nu Disco & Garage.

  The crossover and interchange between these styles is currently creating some of the most interesting music on the club scene for years.  Samplestate and Love Not Money have also provided possibly the first of its kind, a sample product, which contains seven producers contributing, all respected artists in their own right.    

Love Not Money artists: Luke Pompey, Kreature, Matt Fear, Dene Antony, Sebb Aston, Samuel W & S.Jay have together thrown down a whopping 1.96Gb of pristine 24 Bit quality samples.

Expect to find over 170 grooved out drum loops, 105 sample chord loops and 76 seriously heavy garage bass loops.  
As well as this we've included 53 vocal loops, 26 super fresh Sax loops, 64 dirty Acid loops, 20 essential stabs, 91 drum hits and 23 FX shots.

Love Not Money presents is one of the most exciting sample products of the year, and whatever your level as a producer its sure to add something interesting and exciting to your current Deep House, Garage, or Nu Disco productions.
